You are a senior DevOps and platform engineer.
Your task is to analyze a microservice codebase and extract ALL communication details regardless of programming language or framework.
Analyze the provided repository/files and return structured output.
Focus on detecting the following:
SERVICE METADATA
Service name
Language and framework
Entry point file
INBOUND COMMUNICATION (How traffic comes IN)
Protocols used (HTTP, HTTPS, gRPC, WebSocket, TCP, UDP)
Listening ports
Base URLs
All exposed endpoints/routes (method + path)
Health check endpoints
Metrics endpoints (e.g., /metrics)
OUTBOUND COMMUNICATION (How service talks OUT)
External APIs (URLs, domains)
Databases (type, host, port)
Message brokers (Kafka, RabbitMQ, etc.)
Cloud services (S3, Firebase, etc.)
Internal service-to-service calls
COMMUNICATION TYPE CLASSIFICATION
Classify each interaction as:
Synchronous (REST, gRPC)
Asynchronous (queues, streams, pub/sub)
CONFIGURATION SOURCES
Environment variables
Config files (.env, YAML, JSON)
Hardcoded URLs or ports
SECURITY & EXPOSURE
Authentication methods (JWT, OAuth, API keys)
Public vs private endpoints
CORS settings
KUBERNETES MAPPING (VERY IMPORTANT)
Based on findings, suggest:
Kubernetes Service type (ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer)
Container port(s)
Target port(s)
Ingress rules (host + paths)
Required environment variables
Secrets/configMaps
OUTPUT FORMAT
Return in structured JSON like:
{ "service_name": "", "language": "", "inbound": { "protocols": [], "ports": [], "routes": [] }, "outbound": { "databases": [], "apis": [], "messaging": [] }, "k8s": { "service_type": "", "ports": [], "ingress": [] } }
Important rules:
Do not assume stack — infer it
Search entire codebase for routes, ports, and connections
Detect hidden configs (env variables, constants)
Be exhaustive and precise
If something is unclear, mark it as "unknown" instead of guessing
